of literary texts can, and do, engage with these networks. As a whole, the book provides, for the first time, a comprehensive artefactualist account of the nature of fictional entities.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 4aFiktion. 4aLiteratur/Definition. 4aMeinong, Alexander. 4aRealismus. 4adefinition of literature. 4afiction. 4arealism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Language.2bisacsh0 cEPUBz97831106651540 cprintz978311064680140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110648225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110648225.jpg  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK